        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sandbox): create missing skill mount directories to enforce read-only protection",
        "body": "Closes #94425\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nSandbox skill directories were not mounted read-only on first agent creation because `isExistingWorkspaceSkillMountSource` returned `false` when the host directory didn't exist, causing the read-only bind mount to be silently skipped.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nIn the `catch` block (when `lstatSync` throws because the directory doesn't exist), create the directory so the read-only mount is always applied.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { isExistingWorkspaceSkillMountSource } from \"./src/agents/sandbox/workspace-mounts.ts\"; ...'\n\nisExistingWorkspaceSkillMountSource test:\nBefore (no directory): false\nisExistingWorkspaceSkillMountSource: true\nAfter (directory):    true\n```\n\nThe function creates the missing directory (visible by `After` showing `true`). When the directory already exists, behavior is identical (no regression).",
